He also highlighted the importance of making sure that bats live there before the renovation of buildings, as the destruction of a single colony could result in the destruction of 400 females and young individuals, which could lead to the extinction of the entire local population.
Bats are protected animals, their destruction, harassment, and habitat disturbance are prohibited by law.
Elisabeth Ferrell, representative of the Bat Conservation Trust in Scotland, also asked for the help of the population.
