Central Celebes is mainly characterised by fishing and farming, especially in the coastal areas of Donggala.
Nickel mining is an important sector of the economy, but it is concentrated mainly in Morowali, on the other side of Celebes.
According to the Indonesian Disaster Management Agency, Palu and Donggala have been hit several times by tsunamis in the last 100 years.
