2010: A magnitude 7.5 quake shook an island of the Mentawa archipelago near Sumatra and sometimes caused a ten-metre tsunami that destroyed dozens of villages and claimed about 300 lives.
2016: A near-surface quake reached the governorship of Aceh Pidie Jaya. The panic and destruction that followed it reminded many of the memories of the terrible tsunami of 2004.
